            "textContents": [
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                    "paragraphTitle": "Unreal conditionals",
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "1. Second conditional"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We use if + simple past + would/might/could + base form to talk about the consequences of an imagined present or future."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "2. Third conditional"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We use if + past perfect and would/might/could + have + past participle to talk about the past consequences of a hypothetical, different past."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "3. Mixed conditionals"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We can use a mixture of the second and third conditional by using if + past perfect + would/might/could + base form. This is used to imagine the present consequences of a hypothetical, different past."
                    ]
                }
            ],
